[title]
Rules - Smogon Premier League
[header]
[page]

<h2>Rules</h2>

<p>Before battling your opponent, make sure to follow these rules:</p>

<h3>BW OU</h3>

<ul class="long_list">
<li>All BW OU matches must be played on Pokemon Online.</li>
<li>You are not allowed to use Pokémon classified as "Uber".</li>
<li>All tiers are based on <a href="/bw/tiers/">Smogon tiers</a>. The current status of the appropriate standard ladder will be function as the prevailing tier list.</li>
<li>A player may not use any Item / Pokemon / Moveset that is not obtainable in-game.</li>
<li>Using both a Pokemon with Drizzle and a Pokemon with Swift Swim on the same team is banned.</li>
<li>Team Preview must be enabled.</li>
<li>Only Pokemon that have been proven to have a released Dream World ability will be allowed to use that ability.</li>
<li>Species Clause: A player cannot have two of the same Pokémon on their team. For example, a player cannot have two Koffing on his or her team.</li>
<li>Sleep Clause: A player cannot put two or more different opposing Pokémon to sleep using attacks that induce sleep to opposing Pokémon.</li>
<li>Evasion Clause: A player cannot increase their Pokémon's evasion stat with a move that specifically increases evasion. The items BrightPowder and Lax Incense are banned.</li>
<li>OHKO Clause: Players cannot use moves that have a chance of instantly KOing an opposing Pokémon. For example, Horn Drill is an illegal move to have on a Pokémon's move set.</li>
<li>The timer must be on.</li>
<li>"No Spectators" is by default disabled, however, if both players agree to have it on, then you may use this clause. Additionally, if you are asked by either player to remove yourself from the battle and you are not a teammate of either battler, you will respect their request and leave the battle, on the threat of disqualification for that week.</li>
</ul>

<h3>BW Uber</h3>

<ul class="long_list">
<li>All matches must be played on Pokemon Online.</li>
<li>A player may not use any Item / Pokemon / Moveset that is not obtainable in-game.</li>
<li>Team Preview must be enabled.</li>
<li>Only Pokemon that have been proven to have a released Dream World ability will be allowed to use that ability.</li>
<li>The ability Moody may not be used.</li>
<li>Species Clause: A player cannot have two of the same Pokémon on their team. For example, a player cannot have two Koffing on his or her team.</li>
<li>Sleep Clause: A player cannot put two or more different opposing Pokémon to sleep using attacks that induce sleep to opposing Pokémon.</li>
<li>OHKO Clause: Players cannot use moves that have a chance of instantly KOing an opposing Pokémon. For example, Horn Drill is an illegal move to have on a Pokémon's move set.</li>
<li>The timer must be on.</li>
<li>"No Spectators" is by default disabled, however, if both players agree to have it on, then you may use this clause. Additionally, if you are asked by either player to remove yourself from the battle and you are not a teammate of either battler, you will respect their request and leave the battle, on the threat of disqualification for that week.</li>
</ul>

<h3>BW UU</h3>

<ul class="long_list">
<li>All matches must be played on Pokemon Online.</li>
<li>You are not allowed to use Pokémon classified as "Uber", "OU", or "BL".</li>
<li>The abilities Drought and Moody may not be used.</li>
<li>All tiers are based on <a href="/bw/tiers/">Smogon tiers</a>. The current status of the appropriate standard ladder will be function as the prevailing tier list.</li>
<li>Species Clause: A player cannot have two of the same Pokémon on their team. For example, a player cannot have two Koffing on his or her team.</li>
<li>Sleep Clause: A player cannot put two or more different opposing Pokémon to sleep using attacks that induce sleep to opposing Pokémon.</li>
<li>Evasion Clause: A player cannot increase their Pokémon's evasion stat with a move that specifically increases evasion. The items BrightPowder and Lax Incense are banned.</li>
<li>OHKO Clause: Players cannot use moves that have a chance of instantly KOing an opposing Pokémon. For example, Horn Drill is an illegal move to have on a Pokémon's move set.</li>
<li>The timer must be on.</li>
<li>"No Spectators" is by default disabled, however, if both players agree to have it on, then you may use this clause. Additionally, if you are asked by either player to remove yourself from the battle and you are not a teammate of either battler, you will respect their request and leave the battle, on the threat of disqualification for that week.</li>
</ul>

<h3>BW RU</h3>

<ul class="long_list">
<li>All matches must be played on Pokemon Online.</li>
<li>You are not allowed to use Pokémon classified as "Uber", "OU", "BL", "UU", or "BL2".</li>
<li>The abilities Drought and Moody may not be used.</li>
<li>A Pokémon may not have both of the moves Shell Smash and Baton Pass in its moveset.</li>
<li>All tiers are based on <a href="/bw/tiers/">Smogon tiers</a>. The current status of the appropriate standard ladder will be function as the prevailing tier list.</li>
<li>Species Clause: A player cannot have two of the same Pokémon on their team. For example, a player cannot have two Koffing on his or her team.</li>
<li>Sleep Clause: A player cannot put two or more different opposing Pokémon to sleep using attacks that induce sleep to opposing Pokémon.</li>
<li>Evasion Clause: A player cannot increase their Pokémon's evasion stat with a move that specifically increases evasion. The items BrightPowder and Lax Incense are banned.</li>
<li>OHKO Clause: Players cannot use moves that have a chance of instantly KOing an opposing Pokémon. For example, Horn Drill is an illegal move to have on a Pokémon's move set.</li>
<li>The timer must be on.</li>
<li>"No Spectators" is by default disabled, however, if both players agree to have it on, then you may use this clause. Additionally, if you are asked by either player to remove yourself from the battle and you are not a teammate of either battler, you will respect their request and leave the battle, on the threat of disqualification for that week.</li>
</ul>

<h3>DPP OU</h3>

<ul class="long_list">
<li>All matches must be played on Pokemon Online.</li>
<li>You are not allowed to use Pokémon classified as "Uber".</li>
<li>All tiers are based on <a href="/dp/tiers/">Smogon tiers</a>. The current status of the appropriate standard ladder will be function as the prevailing tier list.</li>
<li>Species Clause: A player cannot have two of the same Pokémon on their team. For example, a player cannot have two Koffing on his or her team.</li>
<li>Sleep Clause: A player cannot put two or more different opposing Pokémon to sleep using attacks that induce sleep to opposing Pokémon.</li>
<li>Evasion Clause: A player cannot increase their Pokémon's evasion stat with a move that specifically increases evasion. Items or indirect boosts do not break this clause.</li>
<li>OHKO Clause: Players cannot use moves that have a chance of instantly KOing an opposing Pokémon. For example, Horn Drill is an illegal move to have on a Pokémon's move set.</li>
<li>The timer must be on.</li>
<li>"No Spectators" is by default disabled, however, if both players agree to have it on, then you may use this clause. Additionally, if you are asked by either player to remove yourself from the battle and you are not a teammate of either battler, you will respect their request and leave the battle, on the threat of disqualification for that week.</li>
</ul>

<h3>VGC 2012</h3>

<ul class="long_list">

<li>All matches must be played on Pokemon Online.</li>
<li>The following Pokémon are banned: Mewtwo, Mew, Lugia, Ho-Oh, Celebi, Kyogre, Groudon, Rayquaza, Jirachi, Deoxys (all forms), Dialga, Palkia, Giratina, Phione, Manaphy, Darkrai, Shaymin, Arceus, Victini, Reshiram, Zekrom, Kyurem.</li>
<li>Each match will consist of a best of three series. Whichever player wins two games wins the match.</li>
<li>Players will submit to the host a team of 6 Pokemon / Items they wish to use for a round. These are the only 6 Pokemon / Items they may use during that round. Each player may only bring 4 of these 6 Pokemon / Items into battle. In between matches you are allowed to switch the 4 Pokemon you wish to bring into battle.</li>
<li>All matches are to be played using Wifi Double Battle.</li>
<li>Pokemon should be a maximum of Level 50.</li>
<li>Players can't use two Pokemon with the same Pokedex number or two of the same Item.</li>
<li>Players may not have a Pokemon with Dark Void or Sky Drop in its move set.</li>
<li>Self-KO Clause: Players cannot use moves such as Explosion or Selfdestruct that force a tie. If a move that has recoil damage causes a tie (including from Life Orb), the user of the move is the winner.</li>
<li>The timer must be on.</li>
<li>"No Spectators" is by default disabled, however, if both players agree to have it on, then you may use this clause. Additionally, if you are asked by either player to remove yourself from the battle and you are not a teammate of either battler, you will respect their request and leave the battle, on the threat of disqualification for that week.</li>
</ul>

<h3>ADV OU</h3>

<ul class="long_list">
<li>All matches must be played on Netbattle Supremacy or Pokemon Online.</li>
<li>You are not allowed to use Pokémon classified as "Uber".</li>
<li>All tiers are based on <a href="/rs/tiers/">Smogon tiers</a>.</li>
<li>Species Clause: A player cannot have two of the same Pokémon on their team. For example, a player cannot have two Koffing on his or her team.</li>
<li>Sleep Clause: A player cannot put two or more different opposing Pokémon to sleep using attacks that induce sleep to opposing Pokémon.</li>
<li>Evasion Clause: A player cannot increase their Pokémon's evasion stat with a move that specifically increases evasion. Items or indirect boosts do not break this clause.</li>
<li>OHKO Clause: Players cannot use moves that have a chance of instantly KOing an opposing Pokémon. For example, Horn Drill is an illegal move to have on a Pokémon's move set.</li>
<li>Battle Timeout must be enabled.</li>
<li>"No Spectators" is by default disabled, however, if both players agree to have it on, then you may use this clause. Additionally, if you are asked by either player to remove yourself from the battle and you are not a teammate of either battler, you will respect their request and leave the battle, on the threat of disqualification for that week.</li>
</ul>

<h3>GSC OU</h3>

<ul class="long_list">
<li>All matches must be played on Netbattle Supremacy.</li>
<li>You are not allowed to use Pokémon classified as "Uber".</li>
<li>All tiers are based on <a href="/gs/tiers/">Smogon tiers</a>.</li>
<li>Species Clause: A player cannot have two of the same Pokémon on their team. For example, a player cannot have two Koffing on his or her team.</li>
<li>Sleep Clause: A player cannot put two or more different opposing Pokémon to sleep using attacks that induce sleep to opposing Pokémon.</li>
<li>Evasion Clause: A player cannot increase their Pokémon's evasion stat with a move that specifically increases evasion. Items or indirect boosts do not break this clause.</li>
<li>OHKO Clause: Players cannot use moves that have a chance of instantly KOing an opposing Pokémon. For example, Horn Drill is an illegal move to have on a Pokémon's move set.</li>
<li>Using a trapping move and a Sleep inducing move and Perish Song in combination with each other is banned.</li>
<li>Legendaries are allowed to use Hidden Power.</li>
<li>Battle Timeout must be enabled.</li>
<li>"No Spectators" is by default disabled, however, if both players agree to have it on, then you may use this clause. Additionally, if you are asked by either player to remove yourself from the battle and you are not a teammate of either battler, you will respect their request and leave the battle, on the threat of disqualification for that week.</li>
</ul>

<h3>RBY OU</h3>

<ul class="long_list">
<li>All matches must be played on Netbattle Supremacy.</li>
<li>No GSC tradebacks.</li>
<li>You are not allowed to use Mewtwo or Mew.</li>
<li>Species Clause: A player cannot have two of the same Pokémon on their team. For example, a player cannot have two Koffing on his or her team.</li>
<li>Sleep Clause: A player cannot put two or more different opposing Pokémon to sleep using attacks that induce sleep to opposing Pokémon.</li>
<li>Freeze Clause: A player cannot freeze two or more different opposing Pokémon.</li>
<li>Evasion Clause: A player cannot increase their Pokémon's evasion stat with a move that specifically increases evasion. Indirect boosts do not break this clause.</li>
<li>OHKO Clause: Players cannot use moves that have a chance of instantly KOing an opposing Pokémon. For example, Horn Drill is an illegal move to have on a Pokémon's move set.</li>
<li>Battle Timeout must be enabled.</li>
<li>"No Spectators" is by default disabled, however, if both players agree to have it on, then you may use this clause. Additionally, if you are asked by either player to remove yourself from the battle and you are not a teammate of either battler, you will respect their request and leave the battle, on the threat of disqualification for that week.</li>
</ul>

<p>Violating these rules will earn a loss for your team and may result in you being banned from all future Smogon Premier League seasons.</p>